22 µg/m³—the city's best month. January is comparable. These months offer the most feasible conditions for outdoor activity, though even wet season Jakarta exceeds WHO guidelines.\n\nJakarta's annual median of 42.1 µg/m³ represents 3.6 years of life expectancy lost. Schedule your visit for December through March if outdoor activity or air quality is a concern. Check Kalimantan fire season forecasts: in El Niño years, July–October can be significantly worse than the median suggests."}